        "question": "Find out the correct claims:<br><br>A. An inference is said to be immediate when more than one premise is relied upon for the conclusion.<br>B. Two propositions are contradictories, if one is the denial of the other.<br>C. Sub-contraries, if they cannot be both true though they may both be false.<br>D. Negative propositions distribute their predicate terms.<br>E. Quality of any categorical proposition determines whether its subject term is distributed.<br><br>Choose the correct answer from the options given below:",
